{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775905924993,"sessionID":"ses_283c262f3ffedN6xurQA2NY1Da","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3de367001GQyDF2fkoIj3ck","messageID":"msg_d7c3dc16a001ioS7jmbNqUOUR3","sessionID":"ses_283c262f3ffedN6xurQA2NY1Da","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-7d3a3e792771415689a57afa640751f8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019: CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This module defines the CLI binary entry points for the agentcube system, consisting of four main executables:\n6: \n7: | Binary | Purpose | Module | HTTP Framework |\n8: |--------|---------|--------|----------------|\n9: | `picod` | Local code execution daemon | `pkg/picod` | Gin |\n10: | `router` | Session routing and reverse proxy | `pkg/router` | Gin |\n11: | `workloadmanager` | Workload manager HTTP server | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Chi |\n12: | `agentd` | Agent daemon (idle cleanup controller) | `pkg/agentd` | controller-runtime |\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Architecture\n17: \n18: ### Directory Structure\n19: \n20: ```\n21: cmd/\n22: ├── picod/\n23: │   ├── main.go              # PicoD entry point (implemented)\n24: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n25: ├── router/\n26: │   ├── main.go              # Router entry point\n27: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n28: ├── workloadmanager/\n29: │   ├── main.go              # WorkloadManager entry point\n30: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n31: └── agentd/\n32: │   ├── main.go              # Agentd entry point\n33: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n34: ```\n35: \n36: ### Binary Dependency Graph\n37: \n38: ```\n39: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n40: │                            CLI Binaries                                       │\n41: ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n42: │                                                                               │\n43: │   ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌───────────┐   │\n44: │   │   picod   │     │   router  │     │workloadmanager│     │  agentd   │   │\n45: │   └───────────┘     └───────────┘     └───────────────┘     └───────────┘   │\n46: │        │                 │                     │                   │        │\n47: │        ▼                 ▼                     ▼                   ▼        │\n48: │   ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌───────────┐   │\n49: │   │ pkg/picod │     │pkg/router │     │pkg/workload   │     │pkg/agentd │   │\n50: │   │           │     │           │     │   manager     │     │           │   │\n51: │   └───────────┘     └───────────┘     └───────────────┘     └───────────┘   │\n52: │        │                 │                     │                   │        │\n53: │        ▼                 ▼                     ▼                   ▼        │\n54: │   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n55: │   │                    Common Dependencies                                 │ │\n56: │   │  - k8s.io/klog/v2 (logging)                                           │ │\n57: │   │  - github.com/spf13/pflag (flags)                                     │ │\n58: │   │  - context, os, signal                                                │ │\n59: │   └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n60: │                                                                               │\n61: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ### Deployment Model\n65: \n66: ```\n67: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n68: │                      Kubernetes Cluster                          │\n69: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n70: │                                                                  │\n71: │  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐                  │\n72: │  │ router Deployment│    │workloadmanager   │                  │\n73: │  │    (Pod :8080)   │───▶│ Deployment       │                  │\n74: │  └──────────────────┘    │   (Pod :8080)    │                  │\n75: │           │              └──────────────────┘                  │\n76: │           │                      │                              │\n77: │           ▼                      ▼                              │\n78: │  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐                  │\n79: │  │ Redis/Valkey     │    │  K8s API Server  │                  │\n80: │  │ (Session Store)  │    │  (CRDs, Pods)    │                  │\n81: │  └──────────────────┘    └──────────────────┘                  │\n82: │                                                                  │\n83: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                           │\n84: │  │ agentd Deployment│    (Leader Election enabled)             │\n85: │  │  (Controller)    │                                           │\n86: │  └──────────────────┘                                           │\n87: │                                                                  │\n88: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n89: \n90: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n91: │                      Sandbox Pod                                 │\n92: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n93: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                           │\n94: │  │ picod sidecar    │    (Local code execution)                │\n95: │  │   (Port 8080)    │                                           │\n96: │  └──────────────────┘                                           │\n97: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Data Structures\n103: \n104: ### Common CLI Configuration Pattern\n105: \n106: ```go\n107: package main\n108: \n109: type CLIConfig struct {\n110:     LogLevel    string `flag:\"log-level\" default:\"info\" usage:\"Log level (debug, info, warn, error)\"`\n111:     MetricsAddr string `flag:\"metrics-addr\" default:\"0\" usage:\"Metrics server address (0 to disable)\"`\n112:     HealthAddr  string `flag:\"health-addr\" default:\"\" usage:\"Health check server address\"`\n113: }\n114: ```\n115: \n116: ### PicoD CLI Configuration\n117: \n118: ```go\n119: package main\n120: \n121: type PicoDConfig struct {\n122:     CLIConfig\n123:     Port         int    `flag:\"port\" default:\"8080\" usage:\"HTTP listening port\"`\n124:     Workspace    string `flag:\"workspace\" default:\"\" usage:\"Workspace directory path\"`\n125:     AuthEnabled  bool   `flag:\"auth-enabled\" default:\"true\" usage:\"Enable authentication\"`\n126:     MaxExecTime  int    `flag:\"max-exec-time\" default:\"30\" usage:\"Maximum execution time in seconds\"`\n127:     MaxFileSize  int64  `flag:\"max-file-size\" default:\"10485760\" usage:\"Maximum file size in bytes\"`\n128:     SanitizeRoot string `flag:\"sanitize-root\" default:\"\" usage:\"Root directory for path sanitization\"`\n129: }\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### Router CLI Configuration\n133: \n134: ```go\n135: package main\n136: \n137: type RouterConfig struct {\n138:     CLIConfig\n139:     Port                 string `flag:\"port\" default:\":8080\" usage:\"HTTP listening port\"`\n140:     MaxConcurrentRequests int   `flag:\"max-concurrent\" default:\"1000\" usage:\"Maximum concurrent requests\"`\n141:     Debug                bool   `flag:\"debug\" default:\"false\" usage:\"Enable debug mode\"`\n142:     EnableTLS            bool   `flag:\"enable-tls\" default:\"false\" usage:\"Enable TLS\"`\n143:     TLSCert              string `flag:\"tls-cert\" default:\"\" usage:\"TLS certificate file\"`\n144:     TLSKey               string `flag:\"tls-key\" default:\"\" usage:\"TLS key file\"`\n145:     StoreAddr            string `flag:\"store-addr\" default:\"\" usage:\"Redis/Valkey address\"`\n146:     StorePassword        string `flag:\"store-password\" default:\"\" usage:\"Redis/Valkey password\"`\n147:     StoreType            string `flag:\"store-type\" default:\"redis\" usage:\"Store type (redis, valkey)\"`\n148: }\n149: ```\n150: \n151: ### WorkloadManager CLI Configuration\n152: \n153: ```go\n154: package main\n155: \n156: type WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n157:     CLIConfig\n158:     Addr              string        `flag:\"addr\" default:\":8080\" usage:\"HTTP server address\"`\n159:     ReadTimeout       time.Duration `flag:\"read-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"HTTP read timeout\"`\n160:     WriteTimeout      time.Duration `flag:\"write-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"HTTP write timeout\"`\n161:     IdleTimeout       time.Duration `flag:\"idle-timeout\" default:\"90s\" usage:\"HTTP idle timeout\"`\n162:     ShutdownTimeout   time.Duration `flag:\"shutdown-timeout\" default:\"10s\" usage:\"Graceful shutdown timeout\"`\n163:     GCInterval        time.Duration `flag:\"gc-interval\" default:\"5m\" usage:\"Garbage collection interval\"`\n164:     GCOnceTimeout     time.Duration `flag:\"gc-once-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"Single GC run timeout\"`\n165:     Kubeconfig        string        `flag:\"kubeconfig\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes config file path\"`\n166:     MasterURL         string        `flag:\"master-url\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes API server URL\"`\n167: }\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### Agentd CLI Configuration\n171: \n172: ```go\n173: package main\n174: \n175: type AgentdConfig struct {\n176:     CLIConfig\n177:     IdleThreshold        time.Duration `flag:\"idle-threshold\" default:\"30m\" usage:\"Idle threshold for cleanup\"`\n178:     CheckInterval        time.Duration `flag:\"check-interval\" default:\"5m\" usage:\"Cleanup check interval\"`\n179:     MaxConcurrentCleanup int           `flag:\"max-concurrent\" default:\"10\" usage:\"Maximum concurrent cleanups\"`\n180:     Namespaces           []string      `flag:\"namespace\" default:\"default\" usage:\"Namespaces to watch\"`\n181:     LeaderElection       bool          `flag:\"leader-election\" default:\"true\" usage:\"Enable leader election\"`\n182:     LeaderElectionID     string        `flag:\"leader-election-id\" default:\"agentcube-agentd\" usage:\"Leader election ID\"`\n183:     Kubeconfig           string        `flag:\"kubeconfig\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes config file path\"`\n184: }\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ## API Contracts\n190: \n191: ### Binary Entry Point Interface\n192: \n193: Each binary follows this pattern:\n194: \n195: ```go\n196: package main\n197: \n198: type Binary interface {\n199:     InitFlags() *Config\n200:     ValidateConfig(cfg *Config) error\n201:     Run(ctx context.Context, cfg *Config) error\n202:     Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n203: }\n204: \n205: func main() {\n206:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n207:     flag.Parse()\n208:     \n209:     cfg := InitFlags()\n210:     if err := ValidateConfig(cfg); err != nil {\n211:         klog.Fatalf(\"invalid config: %v\", err)\n212:         os.Exit(1)\n213:     }\n214:     \n215:     ctx, cancel := signal.NotifyContext(context.Background(), syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n216:     defer cancel()\n217:     \n218:     if err := Run(ctx, cfg); err != nil {\n219:         klog.Fatalf(\"run error: %v\", err)\n220:         os.Exit(1)\n221:     }\n222: }\n223: ```\n224: \n225: ### Signal Handling Contract\n226: \n227: ```go\n228: package main\n229: \n230: func setupSignalHandler() context.Context {\n231:     ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n232:     \n233:     c := make(chan os.Signal, 2)\n234:     signal.Notify(c, syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n235:     \n236:     go func() {\n237:         sig := <-c\n238:         klog.InfoS(\"received signal\", \"signal\", sig)\n239:         cancel()\n240:         \n241:         if sig == syscall.SIGKILL {\n242:             <-c\n243:             klog.InfoS(\"received second signal, forcing exit\")\n244:             os.Exit(1)\n245:         }\n246:     }()\n247:     \n248:     return ctx\n249: }\n250: ```\n251: \n252: ### Health Check Contract\n253: \n254: ```go\n255: package main\n256: \n257: type HealthChecker interface {\n258:     Live() bool\n259:     Ready() bool\n260: }\n261: \n262: func (h *HealthServer) Start(addr string) error {\n263:     mux := http.NewServeMux()\n264:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/live\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n265:         if h.Live() {\n266:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n267:             w.Write([]byte(\"OK\"))\n268:         } else {\n269:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n270:         }\n271:     })\n272:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/ready\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n273:         if h.Ready() {\n274:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n275:             w.Write([]byte(\"OK\"))\n276:         } else {\n277:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n278:         }\n279:     })\n280:     return http.ListenAndServe(addr, mux)\n281: }\n282: ```\n283: \n284: ### Flag Registration Contract\n285: \n286: ```go\n287: package main\n288: \n289: func InitFlags() *Config {\n290:     cfg := &Config{}\n291:     \n292:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n293:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n294:     \n295:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.LogLevel, \"log-level\", \"info\", \"Log level\")\n296:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.MetricsAddr, \"metrics-addr\", \"0\", \"Metrics address\")\n297:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.HealthAddr, \"health-addr\", \"\", \"Health address\")\n298:     \n299:     flag.Parse()\n300:     \n301:     return cfg\n302: }\n303: ```\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## Binary Implementation Details\n308: \n309: ### 1. picod (cmd/picod/main.go)\n310: \n311: **Purpose**: Local code execution daemon running as a sidecar in sandbox pods.\n312: \n313: **Current Implementation** (pkg/picod/server.go:26-77):\n314: \n315: ```go\n316: func main() {\n317:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n318:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n319: \n320:     port := flag.Int(\"port\", 8080, \"HTTP listening port\")\n321:     workspace := flag.String(\"workspace\", \"\", \"Workspace directory path\")\n322:     flag.Parse()\n323: \n324:     config := &picod.Config{\n325:         Port:      *port,\n326:         Workspace: *workspace,\n327:     }\n328: \n329:     server, err := picod.NewServer(config)\n330:     if err != nil {\n331:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create server: %v\", err)\n332:         os.Exit(1)\n333:     }\n334: \n335:     if err := server.Run(context.Background()); err != nil {\n336:         klog.Fatalf(\"server error: %v\", err)\n337:         os.Exit(1)\n338:     }\n339: }\n340: ```\n341: \n342: **Endpoints**:\n343: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n344: |------|--------|---------|\n345: | `/health` | GET | Health check |\n346: | `/api/execute` | POST | Execute code |\n347: | `/api/files` | POST | Upload file |\n348: | `/api/files` | GET | List files |\n349: | `/api/files/*path` | GET | Download file |\n350: \n351: ### 2. router (cmd/router/main.go)\n352: \n353: **Purpose**: Session routing and reverse proxy for agent/code interpreter invocations.\n354: \n355: **Implementation Template**:\n356: \n357: ```go\n358: func main() {\n359:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n360:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n361:     \n362:     cfg := &RouterConfig{}\n363:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Port, \"port\", \":8080\", \"HTTP listening port\")\n364:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.StoreAddr, \"store-addr\", \"\", \"Redis/Valkey address\")\n365:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.StoreType, \"store-type\", \"redis\", \"Store type\")\n366:     flag.IntVar(&cfg.MaxConcurrentRequests, \"max-concurrent\", 1000, \"Max concurrent requests\")\n367:     flag.BoolVar(&cfg.Debug, \"debug\", false, \"Enable debug mode\")\n368:     flag.Parse()\n369:     \n370:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n371:     \n372:     store, err := initStore(cfg)\n373:     if err != nil {\n374:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to init store: %v\", err)\n375:     }\n376:     \n377:     sessionManager := router.NewSessionManager(store)\n378:     jwtManager := router.NewJWTManager()\n379:     \n380:     server := router.NewServer(&router.Config{\n381:         Port:                 cfg.Port,\n382:         MaxConcurrentRequests: cfg.MaxConcurrentRequests,\n383:         Debug:                cfg.Debug,\n384:     }, sessionManager, store, jwtManager, klog.Logger{})\n385:     \n386:     if err := server.Start(ctx); err != nil {\n387:         klog.Fatalf(\"router error: %v\", err)\n388:     }\n389: }\n390: ```\n391: \n392: **Endpoints**:\n393: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n394: |------|--------|---------|\n395: | `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe |\n396: | `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe |\n397: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Agent invocation proxy |\n398: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Code interpreter proxy |\n399: \n400: ### 3. workloadmanager (cmd/workloadmanager/main.go)\n401: \n402: **Purpose**: Workload manager HTTP server for sandbox lifecycle management.\n403: \n404: **Implementation Template**:\n405: \n406: ```go\n407: func main() {\n408:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n409:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n410:     \n411:     cfg := &WorkloadManagerConfig{}\n412:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Addr, \"addr\", \":8080\", \"HTTP server address\")\n413:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.ReadTimeout, \"read-timeout\", 30*time.Second, \"Read timeout\")\n414:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.WriteTimeout, \"write-timeout\", 30*time.Second, \"Write timeout\")\n415:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.GCInterval, \"gc-interval\", 5*time.Minute, \"GC interval\")\n416:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Kubeconfig, \"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"Kubeconfig path\")\n417:     flag.Parse()\n418:     \n419:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n420:     \n421:     k8sClient, err := workloadmanager.NewK8sClient(cfg.Kubeconfig, cfg.MasterURL)\n422:     if err != nil {\n423:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create k8s client: %v\", err)\n424:     }\n425:     \n426:     store, err := initStore(cfg)\n427:     if err != nil {\n428:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to init store: %v\", err)\n429:     }\n430:     \n431:     server := workloadmanager.NewHTTPServerWithClients(\n432:         workloadmanager.Config{\n433:             Addr:            cfg.Addr,\n434:             ReadTimeout:     cfg.ReadTimeout,\n435:             WriteTimeout:    cfg.WriteTimeout,\n436:             ShutdownTimeout: cfg.ShutdownTimeout,\n437:         },\n438:         klog.Logger{},\n439:         k8sClient,\n440:         store,\n441:     )\n442:     \n443:     server.RegisterHandler(\"health\", workloadmanager.NewHealthHandler())\n444:     server.RegisterHandler(\"sandbox\", workloadmanager.NewSandboxHandler(k8sClient, store))\n445:     \n446:     server.GracefulShutdown()\n447:     \n448:     errCh := server.Start()\n449:     select {\n450:     case err := <-errCh:\n451:         klog.Fatalf(\"workloadmanager error: %v\", err)\n452:     case <-ctx.Done():\n453:         server.Stop(context.Background())\n454:     }\n455: }\n456: ```\n457: \n458: **Endpoints**:\n459: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n460: |------|--------|---------|\n461: | `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe |\n462: | `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe |\n463: | `/sandboxes` | POST | Create sandbox |\n464: | `/sandboxes/:id` | GET | Get sandbox |\n465: | `/sandboxes/:id` | DELETE | Delete sandbox |\n466: \n467: ### 4. agentd (cmd/agentd/main.go)\n468: \n469: **Purpose**: Kubernetes controller for idle resource cleanup using controller-runtime.\n470: \n471: **Implementation Template**:\n472: \n473: ```go\n474: func main() {\n475:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n476:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n477:     \n478:     cfg := &AgentdConfig{}\n479:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.IdleThreshold, \"idle-threshold\", 30*time.Minute, \"Idle threshold\")\n480:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.CheckInterval, \"check-interval\", 5*time.Minute, \"Check interval\")\n481:     flag.IntVar(&cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup, \"max-concurrent\", 10, \"Max concurrent cleanups\")\n482:     flag.BoolVar(&cfg.LeaderElection, \"leader-election\", true, \"Enable leader election\")\n483:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.LeaderElectionID, \"leader-election-id\", \"agentcube-agentd\", \"Leader election ID\")\n484:     flag.Parse()\n485:     \n486:     k8sConfig, err := ctrl.GetConfig()\n487:     if err != nil {\n488:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to get k8s config: %v\", err)\n489:     }\n490:     \n491:     mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(k8sConfig, ctrl.Options{\n492:         LeaderElection:          cfg.LeaderElection,\n493:         LeaderElectionID:        cfg.LeaderElectionID,\n494:         LeaderElectionNamespace: \"default\",\n495:     })\n496:     if err != nil {\n497:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create manager: %v\", err)\n498:     }\n499:     \n500:     if err := agentd.SetupIdleCleanupController(mgr, cfg); err != nil {\n501:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to setup controller: %v\", err)\n502:     }\n503:     \n504:     klog.InfoS(\"starting agentd controller\")\n505:     if err := mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler()); err != nil {\n506:         klog.Fatalf(\"controller error: %v\", err)\n507:     }\n508: }\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ---\n512: \n513: ## Error Handling\n514: \n515: ### Error Categories\n516: \n517: | Category | Description | Action |\n518: |----------|-------------|--------|\n519: | `ErrConfigInvalid` | Configuration validation failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n520: | `ErrStoreConnect` | Store connection failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n521: | `ErrK8sConnect` | Kubernetes connection failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n522: | `ErrServerStart` | HTTP server start failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n523: | `ErrSignalReceived` | Graceful shutdown triggered | Log info, cancel context |\n524: | `ErrShutdownTimeout` | Shutdown exceeded timeout | Log warning, force exit |\n525: \n526: ### Error Handling Pattern\n527: \n528: ```go\n529: func handleStartupError(component string, err error) {\n530:     if errors.Is(err, context.Canceled) {\n531:         klog.InfoS(\"shutdown requested\")\n532:         return\n533:     }\n534:     \n535:     if errors.Is(err, syscall.SIGTERM) || errors.Is(err, syscall.SIGINT) {\n536:         klog.InfoS(\"received termination signal\", \"signal\", err)\n537:         return\n538:     }\n539:     \n540:     klog.ErrorS(err, \"startup failure\", \"component\", component)\n541:     os.Exit(1)\n542: }\n543: ```\n544: \n545: ### Graceful Shutdown Sequence\n546: \n547: ```\n548: 1. Signal received (SIGTERM/SIGINT)\n549: 2. Cancel main context\n550: 3. Stop accepting new requests\n551: 4. Wait for in-flight requests (timeout configurable)\n552: 5. Close store connections\n553: 6. Close K8s client connections\n554: 7. Exit with code 0\n555: ```\n556: \n557: ### Validation Errors\n558: \n559: ```go\n560: func ValidateConfig(cfg *Config) error {\n561:     if cfg.Port <= 0 || cfg.Port > 65535 {\n562:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid port: %d\", cfg.Port)\n563:     }\n564:     \n565:     if cfg.IdleThreshold < 0 {\n566:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid idle threshold: %v\", cfg.IdleThreshold)\n567:     }\n568:     \n569:     if cfg.CheckInterval < 0 {\n570:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid check interval: %v\", cfg.CheckInterval)\n571:     }\n572:     \n573:     if cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup < 0 {\n574:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid max concurrent cleanup: %d\", cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup)\n575:     }\n576:     \n577:     return nil\n578: }\n579: ```\n580: \n581: ---\n582: \n583: ## Testing Strategy\n584: \n585: ### Unit Tests\n586: \n587: #### Flag Parsing Tests\n588: \n589: ```go\n590: func TestInitFlags(t *testing.T) {\n591:     tests := []struct {\n592:         name     string\n593:         args     []string\n594:         expected *Config\n595:     }{\n596:         {\n597:             name: \"default values\",\n598:             args: []string{},\n599:             expected: &Config{\n600:                 Port:           8080,\n601:                 LogLevel:       \"info\",\n602:                 IdleThreshold:  30 * time.Minute,\n603:             },\n604:         },\n605:         {\n606:             name: \"custom port\",\n607:             args: []string{\"-port\", \"9000\"},\n608:             expected: &Config{\n609:                 Port:          9000,\n610:             },\n611:         },\n612:         {\n613:             name: \"multiple flags\",\n614:             args: []string{\"-port\", \"9000\", \"-debug\", \"true\"},\n615:             expected: &Config{\n616:                 Port:  9000,\n617:                 Debug: true,\n618:             },\n619:         },\n620:     }\n621:     \n622:     for _, tt := range tests {\n623:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n624:             fs := flag.NewFlagSet(\"test\", flag.ContinueOnError)\n625:             cfg := &Config{}\n626:             setupFlags(fs, cfg)\n627:             \n628:             err := fs.Parse(tt.args)\n629:             require.NoError(t, err)\n630:             \n631:             assert.Equal(t, tt.expected.Port, cfg.Port)\n632:         })\n633:     }\n634: }\n635: ```\n636: \n637: #### Signal Handler Tests\n638: \n639: ```go\n640: func TestSignalHandler(t *testing.T) {\n641:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n642:     \n643:     syscall.Kill(syscall.Getpid(), syscall.SIGTERM)\n644:     \n645:     select {\n646:     case <-ctx.Done():\n647:         assert.True(t, true)\n648:     case <-time.After(5 * time.Second):\n649:         t.Fatal(\"signal handler did not cancel context\")\n650:     }\n651: }\n652: ```\n653: \n654: #### Config Validation Tests\n655: \n656: ```go\n657: func TestValidateConfig(t *testing.T) {\n658:     tests := []struct {\n659:         name        string\n660:         config      *Config\n661:         expectError bool\n662:     }{\n663:         {\n664:             name: \"valid config\",\n665:             config: &Config{\n666:                 Port:          8080,\n667:                 IdleThreshold: 30 * time.Minute,\n668:             },\n669:             expectError: false,\n670:         },\n671:         {\n672:             name: \"invalid port\",\n673:             config: &Config{\n674:                 Port: -1,\n675:             },\n676:             expectError: true,\n677:         },\n678:         {\n679:             name: \"invalid idle threshold\",\n680:             config: &Config{\n681:                 IdleThreshold: -1 * time.Minute,\n682:             },\n683:             expectError: true,\n684:         },\n685:     }\n686:     \n687:     for _, tt := range tests {\n688:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n689:             err := ValidateConfig(tt.config)\n690:             if tt.expectError {\n691:                 assert.Error(t, err)\n692:             } else {\n693:                 assert.NoError(t, err)\n694:             }\n695:         })\n696:     }\n697: }\n698: ```\n699: \n700: ### Integration Tests\n701: \n702: #### Binary Startup Tests\n703: \n704: ```go\n705: func TestBinaryStartup(t *testing.T) {\n706:     if testing.Short() {\n707:         t.Skip(\"skipping integration test\")\n708:     }\n709:     \n710:     binary := buildBinary(t, \"picod\")\n711:     \n712:     cmd := exec.Command(binary, \"-port\", \"18080\")\n713:     cmd.Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}\n714:     cmd.Stderr = &bytes.Buffer{}\n715:     \n716:     err := cmd.Start()\n717:     require.NoError(t, err)\n718:     \n719:     defer cmd.Process.Kill()\n720:     \n721:     assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n722:         resp, err := http.Get(\"http://localhost:18080/health\")\n723:         if err != nil {\n724:             return false\n725:         }\n726:         defer resp.Body.Close()\n727:         return resp.StatusCode == http.StatusOK\n728:     }, 10*time.Second, 100*time.Millisecond)\n729: }\n730: ```\n731: \n732: #### Graceful Shutdown Tests\n733: \n734: ```go\n735: func TestGracefulShutdown(t *testing.T) {\n736:     binary := buildBinary(t, \"router\")\n737:     \n738:     cmd := exec.Command(binary, \"-port\", \":18080\", \"-store-type\", \"memory\")\n739:     cmd.Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}\n740:     cmd.Stderr = &bytes.Buffer{}\n741:     \n742:     err := cmd.Start()\n743:     require.NoError(t, err)\n744:     \n745:     waitForHealthy(t, \"http://localhost:18080/health/live\")\n746:     \n747:     syscall.Kill(cmd.Process.Pid, syscall.SIGTERM)\n748:     \n749:     done := make(chan error, 1)\n750:     go func() {\n751:         done <- cmd.Wait()\n752:     }()\n753:     \n754:     select {\n755:     case err := <-done:\n756:         assert.NoError(t, err)\n757:     case <-time.After(15 * time.Second):\n758:         t.Fatal(\"binary did not shutdown within timeout\")\n759:     }\n760: }\n761: ```\n762: \n763: ### Build Tests\n764: \n765: ```go\n766: func TestBuildAllBinaries(t *testing.T) {\n767:     binaries := []string{\"picod\", \"router\", \"workloadmanager\", \"agentd\"}\n768:     \n769:     for _, binary := range binaries {\n770:         t.Run(binary, func(t *testing.T) {\n771:             cmd := exec.Command(\"go\", \"build\", \"-o\", \"/tmp/\"+binary, \"./cmd/\"+binary)\n772:             output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n773:             assert.NoError(t, err, \"build output: %s\", output)\n774:             \n775:             assert.FileExists(t, \"/tmp/\"+binary)\n776:         })\n777:     }\n778: }\n779: ```\n780: \n781: ---\n782: \n783: ## Metrics\n784: \n785: ### Prometheus Metrics\n786: \n787: ```go\n788: var (\n789:     startupDuration = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n790:         prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n791:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_startup_duration_seconds\",\n792:             Help: \"Time taken for binary startup\",\n793:         },\n794:         []string{\"binary\"},\n795:     )\n796:     \n797:     shutdownDuration = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n798:         prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n799:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_shutdown_duration_seconds\",\n800:             Help: \"Time taken for graceful shutdown\",\n801:         },\n802:         []string{\"binary\"},\n803:     )\n804:     \n805:     configReloadCount = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n806:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n807:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_config_reload_total\",\n808:             Help: \"Number of configuration reloads\",\n809:         },\n810:         []string{\"binary\"},\n811:     )\n812: )\n813: ```\n814: \n815: ---\n816: \n817: ## Configuration\n818: \n819: ### Environment Variables\n820: \n821: | Variable | Binary | Purpose |\n822: |----------|--------|---------|\n823: | `PORT` | picod, router, workloadmanager | HTTP port override |\n824: | `WORKSPACE` | picod | Workspace directory |\n825: | `STORE_ADDR` | router, workloadmanager | Redis/Valkey address |\n826: | `STORE_TYPE` | router, workloadmanager | Store backend type |\n827: | `KUBECONFIG` | workloadmanager, agentd | Kubernetes config path |\n828: | `LOG_LEVEL` | all | Log level override |\n829: \n830: ### Command-Line Flags Summary\n831: \n832: | Flag | Default | Purpose |\n833: |------|---------|---------|\n834: | `-port` | 8080 | HTTP listening port |\n835: | `-workspace` | current dir | Workspace directory (picod) |\n836: | `-idle-threshold` | 30m | Idle cleanup threshold (agentd) |\n837: | `-check-interval` | 5m | Cleanup check interval (agentd) |\n838: | `-leader-election` | true | Enable leader election (agentd) |\n839: | `-kubeconfig` | in-cluster | Kubernetes config path |\n840: | `-debug` | false | Enable debug mode (router) |\n841: | `-metrics-addr` | 0 | Prometheus metrics address |\n842: \n843: ---\n844: \n845: ## Build Configuration\n846: \n847: ### Go Module\n848: \n849: ```go\n850: // go.mod\n851: module github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n852: \n853: go 1.24\n854: \n855: require (\n856:     github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.x\n857:     github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 v5.x\n858:     k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.x\n859:     sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.19.x\n860: )\n861: ```\n862: \n863: ### Makefile Targets\n864: \n865: ```makefile\n866: .PHONY: build clean\n867: \n868: build:\n869: \tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n870: \tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n871: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n872: \tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n873: \n874: clean:\n875: \trm -rf bin/\n876: \n877: build-picod:\n878: \tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n879: \n880: build-router:\n881: \tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n882: \n883: build-workloadmanager:\n884: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n885: \n886: build-agentd:\n887: \tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n888: ```\n889: \n890: ### Docker Build\n891: \n892: ```dockerfile\n893: # Dockerfile for picod\n894: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n895: WORKDIR /app\n896: COPY . .\n897: RUN go build -o /picod ./cmd/picod\n898: \n899: FROM alpine:3.19\n900: COPY --from=builder /picod /picod\n901: ENTRYPOINT [\"/picod\"]\n902: ```\n903: \n904: ---\n905: \n906: ## Implementation Checklist\n907: \n908: - [x] `cmd/picod/main.go` - PicoD entry point (implemented)\n909: - [ ] `cmd/router/main.go` - Router entry point\n910: - [ ] `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` - WorkloadManager entry point\n911: - [ ] `cmd/agentd/main.go` - Agentd entry point\n912: - [ ] Common signal handling package\n913: - [ ] Common flag validation utilities\n914: - [ ] Health check server integration\n915: - [ ] Metrics server integration\n916: - [ ] Unit tests for flag parsing\n917: - [ ] Unit tests for config validation\n918: - [ ] Integration tests for binary startup\n919: - [ ] Integration tests for graceful shutdown\n920: - [ ] Makefile build targets\n921: - [ ] Docker build configurations\n922: - [ ] Helm deployment manifests\n923: \n924: ---\n925: \n926: ## Dependencies\n927: \n928: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n929: |---------|---------|---------|\n930: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n931: | `github.com/spf13/pflag` | v1.x | POSIX/GNU-style flags |\n932: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.19.x | Controller utilities (agentd) |\n933: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.x | HTTP framework (picod, router) |\n934: | `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | v5.x | HTTP framework (workloadmanager) |\n935: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.x | Metrics |\n\n(End of file - total 935 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019: CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis module defines the CLI binary entry points for the agentcube system, consisting of four main executables:\n\n| Binary | Purpose | Module | HTTP Framework |\n|--------|---------|--------|----------------|\n| `picod` | Local code execution daemon | `pkg/picod` | Gin |\n| `router` | Session routing and reverse proxy | `pkg/router` | Gin |\n| `workloadmanager` | Workload manager HTTP server | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Chi |\n| `agentd` | Agent daemon (idle cleanup controller) | `pkg/agentd` | controller-runtime |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775905924968,"end":1775905924990}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775905924996,"sessionID":"ses_283c262f3ffedN6xurQA2NY1Da","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3de743001S0SW7cRgFYMbFZ","messageID":"msg_d7c3dc16a001ioS7jmbNqUOUR3","sessionID":"ses_283c262f3ffedN6xurQA2NY1Da","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d5ba9204e57644fbbca2c55dadb43546","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: E2E Integration Tests for client-go\n2: \n3: **AR:** AR-041 — E2E 集成测试  \n4: **Module:** test/e2e  \n5: **Language:** Go  \n6: **Size:** L\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## OpenSpec Format\n11: \n12: Each requirement follows GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure for acceptance scenarios.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## REQ-001: Clientset Construction and Interface Compliance\n17: \n18: ### Description\n19: \n20: Clientset must be constructable from REST config and implement the Interface correctly.\n21: \n22: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n23: \n24: #### Scenario: Create Clientset from REST config\n25: - **GIVEN** a valid Kubernetes REST config with cluster endpoint and credentials\n26: - **WHEN** `NewForConfig` is called with the config\n27: - **THEN** a non-nil `*Clientset` is returned with no error\n28: - **AND** the clientset implements the `Interface` interface\n29: - **AND** `RuntimeV1alpha1()` returns a valid `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Create Clientset with custom HTTP client\n32: - **GIVEN** a valid REST config and a custom `*http.Client` with custom timeouts\n33: - **WHEN** `NewForConfigAndClient` is called\n34: - **THEN** the returned `*Clientset` uses the provided HTTP client\n35: - **AND** all API calls use the custom client configuration\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Clientset Discovery interface works\n38: - **GIVEN** a Clientset connected to a running Kubernetes cluster\n39: - **WHEN** `Discovery()` is called\n40: - **THEN** the returned `DiscoveryInterface` can list API groups\n41: - **AND** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` is discoverable\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Panics on invalid config with NewForConfigOrDie\n44: - **GIVEN** an invalid REST config (nil or missing required fields)\n45: - **WHEN** `NewForConfigOrDie` is called\n46: - **THEN** the function panics\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## REQ-002: AgentRuntime CRUD Operations\n51: \n52: ### Description\n53: \n54: AgentRuntimeInterface must support full CRUD lifecycle against a live cluster.\n55: \n56: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Create an AgentRuntime resource\n59: - **GIVEN** a Clientset connected to a Kubernetes cluster with CRDs installed\n60: - **AND** a valid `AgentRuntime` spec in namespace `test-ns`\n61: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})` is called\n62: - **THEN** the returned `AgentRuntime` has the correct name and namespace\n63: - **AND** the resource exists in the cluster with `kubectl get agentruntime`\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Get an existing AgentRuntime\n66: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-agent` exists in namespace `test-ns`\n67: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Get(ctx, \"test-agent\", metav1.GetOptions{})` is called\n68: - **THEN** the returned `AgentRuntime` has name `test-agent`\n69: - **AND** the spec matches the created resource\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: List AgentRuntimes in namespace\n72: - **GIVEN** three AgentRuntimes exist in namespace `test-ns`\n73: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})` is called\n74: - **THEN** the returned `AgentRuntimeList` contains exactly 3 items\n75: - **AND** all items have namespace `test-ns`\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: List AgentRuntimes with label selector\n78: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes exist with labels `app=test` and `app=prod`\n79: - **WHEN** `List` is called with `ListOptions{LabelSelector: \"app=test\"}`\n80: - **THEN** only AgentRuntimes with `app=test` label are returned\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Update an AgentRuntime\n83: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-agent` exists with `spec.replicas=1`\n84: - **WHEN** the spec is updated to `replicas=3` and `Update` is called\n85: - **THEN** the returned AgentRuntime has `spec.replicas=3`\n86: - **AND** the resource in cluster reflects the update\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: UpdateStatus subresource\n89: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with empty status\n90: - **WHEN** `UpdateStatus` is called with status conditions set\n91: - **THEN** only the status subresource is updated\n92: - **AND** the spec remains unchanged\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Delete an AgentRuntime\n95: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-agent` exists\n96: - **WHEN** `Delete(ctx, \"test-agent\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})` is called\n97: - **THEN** the error is nil\n98: - **AND** subsequent `Get` returns a `NotFound` error\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: DeleteCollection with selector\n101: - **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntimes exist with label `cleanup=true`\n102: - **WHEN** `DeleteCollection` is called with matching label selector\n103: - **THEN** all matching resources are deleted\n104: - **AND** non-matching resources remain\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: Patch an AgentRuntime\n107: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `spec.replicas=1`\n108: - **WHEN** `Patch` is called with `MergePatchType` and JSON patch data `{\"spec\":{\"replicas\":5}}`\n109: - **THEN** the AgentRuntime is updated with `spec.replicas=5`\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: Watch AgentRuntime changes\n112: - **GIVEN** a Watch is started with `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n113: - **WHEN** an AgentRuntime is created, updated, and deleted\n114: - **THEN** the watch channel receives `ADDED`, `MODIFIED`, and `DELETED` events respectively\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ## REQ-003: CodeInterpreter CRUD Operations\n119: \n120: ### Description\n121: \n122: CodeInterpreterInterface must support full CRUD lifecycle against a live cluster.\n123: \n124: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: Create a CodeInterpreter resource\n127: - **GIVEN** a Clientset and valid `CodeInterpreter` spec\n128: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreters(\"test-ns\").Create(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.CreateOptions{})` is called\n129: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter is created in the cluster\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Full CRUD cycle for CodeInterpreter\n132: - **GIVEN** a clean namespace\n133: - **WHEN** Create, Get, Update, UpdateStatus, List, and Delete operations are performed\n134: - **THEN** all operations complete successfully\n135: - **AND** the final state matches expectations\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreter events\n138: - **GIVEN** a Watch is started for CodeInterpreters\n139: - **WHEN** multiple CodeInterpreters are created concurrently\n140: - **THEN** all `ADDED` events are received on the watch channel\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter List across namespaces\n143: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreters exist in namespaces `ns-a` and `ns-b`\n144: - **WHEN** `List` is called in each namespace\n145: - **THEN** correct resources are returned per namespace\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## REQ-004: SharedInformerFactory Operations\n150: \n151: ### Description\n152: \n153: SharedInformerFactory must correctly start, sync, and shutdown informers.\n154: \n155: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Start and Shutdown informer factory\n158: - **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` with a Clientset\n159: - **WHEN** `Start(stopCh)` is called\n160: - **THEN** informers begin syncing\n161: - **AND** calling `Shutdown()` stops all informers gracefully\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: WaitForCacheSync reports sync status\n164: - **GIVEN** a SharedInformerFactory with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter informers\n165: - **WHEN** `WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)` is called\n166: - **THEN** the returned map contains `true` for both types\n167: - **AND** all caches are synced with the cluster\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime informer and lister work together\n170: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime informer started and synced\n171: - **AND** an AgentRuntime `test-ar` exists in `test-ns`\n172: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes().Lister().AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Get(\"test-ar\")` is called\n173: - **THEN** the AgentRuntime is returned from cache (no API call)\n174: - **AND** the object matches the cluster state\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter informer and lister work together\n177: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter informer started and synced\n178: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreters().Lister().List(labels.Everything())` is called\n179: - **THEN** all CodeInterpreters across namespaces are returned from cache\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Namespace-scoped informer factory\n182: - **GIVEN** `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions` with `WithNamespace(\"limited-ns\")`\n183: - **WHEN** informers are started\n184: - **THEN** only resources in `limited-ns` are cached\n185: - **AND** resources in other namespaces are not visible to the lister\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Custom resync period\n188: - **GIVEN** a factory created with `defaultResync=30*time.Second`\n189: - **WHEN** informers run for longer than resync period\n190: - **THEN** full resync events are triggered periodically\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: ForResource returns correct informer\n193: - **GIVEN** a SharedInformerFactory\n194: - **WHEN** `ForResource(v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\"))` is called\n195: - **THEN** a GenericInformer for AgentRuntimes is returned\n196: - **AND** the informer is the same instance as from `Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()`\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: TweakListOptions filters list calls\n199: - **GIVEN** a factory with `WithTweakListOptions` that sets `LabelSelector`\n200: - **WHEN** the informer performs list operations\n201: - **THEN** only resources matching the selector are cached\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## REQ-005: Lister Operations\n206: \n207: ### Description\n208: \n209: Listers must provide efficient cached access to resources.\n210: \n211: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeLister lists across namespaces\n214: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes in namespaces `ns-a` and `ns-b`\n215: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeLister.List(labels.Everything())` is called\n216: - **THEN** all AgentRuntimes from both namespaces are returned\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister filters by namespace\n219: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes in namespaces `ns-a` and `ns-b`\n220: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"ns-a\").List(labels.Everything())` is called\n221: - **THEN** only AgentRuntimes in `ns-a` are returned\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Lister returns error for non-existent resource\n224: - **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime named `nonexistent` in namespace `test-ns`\n225: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Get(\"nonexistent\")` is called\n226: - **THEN** an error is returned (not nil)\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterLister mirrors AgentRuntimeLister behavior\n229: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreters in multiple namespaces\n230: - **WHEN** both `List` and `Get` operations are performed\n231: - **THEN** behavior matches AgentRuntimeLister patterns\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Lister List with label selector\n234: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes with various labels\n235: - **WHEN** `List` is called with a label selector\n236: - **THEN** only matching resources are returned\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## REQ-006: Fake Clientset for Unit Testing\n241: \n242: ### Description\n243: \n244: Fake clientset must track objects and support testing patterns.\n245: \n246: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: Fake clientset tracks objects\n249: - **GIVEN** `NewSimpleClientset()` creates an empty fake clientset\n250: - **WHEN** AgentRuntimes are created via the fake client\n251: - **THEN** `List` returns all created objects\n252: - **AND** no actual API calls are made\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Fake clientset returns injected errors\n255: - **GIVEN** a fake clientset with a reactor that returns errors\n256: - **WHEN** Create/Update/Delete operations are called\n257: - **THEN** the injected error is returned\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: Fake clientset supports Watch\n260: - **GIVEN** a fake clientset with an AgentRuntime\n261: - **WHEN** `Watch` is called and the object is modified via the fake client\n262: - **THEN** watch events are generated and sent to the watcher\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Fake clientset AddReactor captures actions\n265: - **GIVEN** a fake clientset with an AddReactor for \"create\"\n266: - **WHEN** Create is called\n267: - **THEN** the reactor captures the action\n268: - **AND** custom behavior can be implemented\n269: \n270: ---\n271: \n272: ## REQ-007: Error Handling and Edge Cases\n273: \n274: ### Description\n275: \n276: Client must handle Kubernetes API errors correctly.\n277: \n278: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Context cancellation aborts operations\n281: - **GIVEN** a context that is cancelled before API call completes\n282: - **WHEN** any CRUD operation is called with the cancelled context\n283: - **THEN** the operation returns a context cancellation error\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: NotFound error for missing resource\n286: - **GIVEN** no resource named `missing` exists\n287: - **WHEN** `Get(ctx, \"missing\", metav1.GetOptions{})` is called\n288: - **THEN** a `*errors.StatusError` with status code 404 is returned\n289: \n290: #### Scenario: AlreadyExists error on duplicate create\n291: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime `duplicate` already exists\n292: - **WHEN** `Create` is called with the same name\n293: - **THEN** an `AlreadyExists` error is returned\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: Invalid field errors are structured\n296: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with an invalid spec field\n297: - **WHEN** `Create` is called\n298: - **THEN** the error can be cast to `*errors.StatusError`\n299: - **AND** `Status().Details.Causes` contains field-level error details\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: Timeout error on slow API\n302: - **GIVEN** a context with short deadline\n303: - **AND** API server is slow\n304: - **WHEN** operation is called\n305: - **THEN** timeout error is returned\n306: \n307: ---\n308: \n309: ## REQ-008: Concurrent Operations\n310: \n311: ### Description\n312: \n313: Client must handle concurrent operations safely.\n314: \n315: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n316: \n317: #### Scenario: Concurrent creates succeed with unique names\n318: - **GIVEN** a Clientset and 10 goroutines each creating an AgentRuntime\n319: - **AND** each goroutine uses a unique name\n320: - **WHEN** all goroutines complete\n321: - **THEN** all 10 AgentRuntimes exist in the cluster\n322: \n323: #### Scenario: Concurrent reads from informer cache\n324: - **GIVEN** an informer with synced cache\n325: - **WHEN** 100 concurrent `Lister.Get` calls are made\n326: - **THEN** all calls complete without race conditions\n327: - **AND** data remains consistent\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: Watch handles high event throughput\n330: - **GIVEN** a Watch started on AgentRuntimes\n331: - **WHEN** 100 AgentRuntimes are created rapidly\n332: - **THEN** all 100 `ADDED` events are received\n333: - **AND** no events are dropped\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Concurrent updates with conflict resolution\n336: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with multiple concurrent updates\n337: - **WHEN** some updates conflict due to resource version\n338: - **THEN** conflict errors are returned for stale updates\n339: - **AND** retry succeeds with fresh resource version\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ## REQ-009: Resource Version and Optimistic Concurrency\n344: \n345: ### Description\n346: \n347: Client must support Kubernetes optimistic concurrency control.\n348: \n349: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n350: \n351: #### Scenario: Update fails with stale resource version\n352: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `resourceVersion=v1`\n353: - **AND** the resource was updated by another client (now `v2`)\n354: - **WHEN** an Update is attempted with `resourceVersion=v1`\n355: - **THEN** a conflict error is returned\n356: - **AND** the error status code is 409\n357: \n358: #### Scenario: Get with ResourceVersion returns consistent snapshot\n359: - **GIVEN** a valid `resourceVersion` from a previous list\n360: - **WHEN** `Get` is called with `metav1.GetOptions{ResourceVersion: rv}`\n361: - **THEN** the data is consistent with that resource version\n362: \n363: #### Scenario: List with ResourceVersion\n364: - **GIVEN** a resourceVersion from a previous list\n365: - **WHEN** `List` is called with that ResourceVersion\n366: - **THEN** response includes matching ResourceVersion\n367: - **AND** data is consistent with requested version\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## REQ-010: Integration with Kubernetes Ecosystem\n372: \n373: ### Description\n374: \n375: client-go must integrate with common Kubernetes patterns and tools.\n376: \n377: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: Works with controller-runtime\n380: - **GIVEN** a controller-runtime Manager\n381: - **WHEN** the client-go Clientset is used alongside controller-runtime\n382: - **THEN** both clients can operate on the same AgentRuntime resources\n383: - **AND** no conflicts occur\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: Informer integrates with workqueue\n386: - **GIVEN** an informer and a `workqueue.TypedRateLimitingInterface`\n387: - **WHEN** an Add/Update/Delete handler enqueues the key\n388: - **THEN** the workqueue processes keys in order with rate limiting\n389: \n390: #### Scenario: Metrics endpoint exposes informer stats\n391: - **GIVEN** a metrics registry and an informer factory\n392: - **WHEN** informer metrics are registered\n393: - **THEN** cache hits, misses, and sync duration are exposed as metrics\n394: \n395: #### Scenario: Leader election with informer factory\n396: - **GIVEN** a leader election lock\n397: - **WHEN** leader is elected\n398: - **THEN** informer factory starts\n399: - **AND** when leader lost, factory shuts down\n400: \n401: ---\n402: \n403: ## Summary\n404: \n405: | REQ ID | Component | Test Count |\n406: |--------|-----------|------------|\n407: | REQ-001 | Clientset Construction | 4 |\n408: | REQ-002 | AgentRuntime CRUD | 10 |\n409: | REQ-003 | CodeInterpreter CRUD | 4 |\n410: | REQ-004 | SharedInformerFactory | 8 |\n411: | REQ-005 | Lister Operations | 5 |\n412: | REQ-006 | Fake Clientset | 4 |\n413: | REQ-007 | Error Handling | 5 |\n414: | REQ-008 | Concurrent Operations | 4 |\n415: | REQ-009 | Resource Version | 3 |\n416: | REQ-010 | Ecosystem Integration | 4 |\n417: \n418: **Total Scenarios:** 51\n419: \n420: ---\n421: \n422: ## Test Infrastructure\n423: \n424: ### E2E Test Setup\n425: \n426: ```go\n427: // test/e2e/e2e_test.go\n428: package e2e\n429: \n430: import (\n431:     \"testing\"\n432:     \"time\"\n433:     \n434:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n435:     clientset \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n436:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions\"\n437:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n438:     \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n439: )\n440: \n441: func newTestClientset(t *testing.T) clientset.Interface {\n442:     loadingRules := clientcmd.NewDefaultClientConfigLoadingRules()\n443:     configOverrides := &clientcmd.ConfigOverrides{}\n444:     config, err := clientcmd.NewNonInteractiveDeferredLoadingClientConfig(\n445:         loadingRules, configOverrides).ClientConfig()\n446:     if err != nil {\n447:         t.Fatalf(\"Failed to load kubeconfig: %v\", err)\n448:     }\n449:     cs, err := clientset.NewForConfig(config)\n450:     if err != nil {\n451:         t.Fatalf(\"Failed to create clientset: %v\", err)\n452:     }\n453:     return cs\n454: }\n455: \n456: func newTestAgentRuntime(name, namespace string) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime {\n457:     return &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n458:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n459:             Name:      name,\n460:             Namespace: namespace,\n461:         },\n462:     }\n463: }\n464: \n465: func newTestCodeInterpreter(name, namespace string) *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter {\n466:     return &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n467:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n468:             Name:      name,\n469:             Namespace: namespace,\n470:         },\n471:     }\n472: }\n473: ```\n474: \n475: ### Test Tags\n476: \n477: ```go\n478: // +build e2e\n479: // Run: go test -tags=e2e ./test/e2e/...\n480: ```\n481: \n482: ---\n483: \n484: ## Dependencies\n485: \n486: | Dependency | Purpose |\n487: |------------|---------|\n488: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Kubernetes client library |\n489: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | API machinery |\n490: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated client |\n491: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Controller patterns (optional) |\n492: \n493: ---\n494: \n495: ## Validation Checklist\n496: \n497: - [ ] Clientset construction from REST config\n498: - [ ] AgentRuntime CRUD operations against live cluster\n499: - [ ] CodeInterpreter CRUD operations against live cluster\n500: - [ ] SharedInformerFactory Start/Shutdown/WaitForCacheSync\n501: - [ ] Informer integration with Listers\n502: - [ ] Namespace-scoped informer filtering\n503: - [ ] Lister Get/List operations\n504: - [ ] Fake clientset object tracking\n505: - [ ] Error handling (NotFound, AlreadyExists, Conflict)\n506: - [ ] Context cancellation handling\n507: - [ ] Concurrent operations safety\n508: - [ ] Watch event reception\n509: - [ ] Resource version conflict detection\n510: - [ ] Integration with controller-runtime\n511: - [ ] Integration with workqueue patterns\n\n(End of file - total 511 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: E2E Integration Tests for client-go\n\n**AR:** AR-041 — E2E 集成测试  \n**Module:** test/e2e  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## OpenSpec Format\n\nEach requirement follows GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure for acceptance scenarios.\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: Clientset Construction and Interface Compliance\n\n### Description\n\nClientset must be constructable from REST config and implement the Interface correctly.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775905924971,"end":1775905924994}}}}
