{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775906172533,"sessionID":"ses_283c262f3ffedN6xurQA2NY1Da","part":{"id":"prt_d7c41adf8001p3JBSGcJhgKCFV","messageID":"msg_d7c3ed610001lm4Rdk5uGUEQ4C","sessionID":"ses_283c262f3ffedN6xurQA2NY1Da","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-9fc2339b382747889d18a9d1ca658763","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/docs/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: Architecture Design Documentation & API Documentation\n\n**AR:** AR-043 — 架构设计文档与 API 文档  \n**Module:** docs  \n**Language:** Markdown  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## OpenSpec Format\n\nEach requirement follows GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure for acceptance scenarios.\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: System Architecture Overview Documentation\n\n### Description\n\nProvide comprehensive system architecture documentation explaining AgentCube's core components, deployment topology, and interaction flows.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Architecture overview page exists\n- **GIVEN** the Docusaurus documentation site at `docs/docs/architecture/`\n- **WHEN** a user navigates to the architecture overview page\n- **THEN** a file `overview.md` exists in the architecture directory\n- **AND** the page renders successfully in Docusaurus\n- **AND** the content includes high-level system purpose and tech stack\n\n#### Scenario: Architecture includes component diagram\n- **GIVEN** the architecture overview documentation\n- **WHEN** the document is viewed\n- **THEN** an ASCII or Mermaid diagram shows the system topology:\n  - Router ↔ Redis/Valkey ↔ WorkloadManager ↔ K8s API\n  - Sandbox Pods with PicoD daemon\n  - Agentd idle cleanup controller\n- **AND** the diagram uses clear component labels and arrows showing data flow\n\n#### Scenario: Tech stack table is documented\n- **GIVEN** the architecture overview page\n- **WHEN** the tech stack section is viewed\n- **THEN** a table lists each technology layer:\n  - Go 1.24 for server components\n  - Python ≥3.10 for CLI/SDK\n  - Gin (Go HTTP framework)\n  - Kubernetes CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`)\n  - Redis/Valkey for session storage\n  - JWT RS256 for authentication\n- **AND** each technology has a purpose column explaining its role\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment topology is explained\n- **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n- **WHEN** the deployment topology section is viewed\n- **THEN** the document describes three deployment patterns:\n  1. Router as Deployment (Pod :8080)\n  2. WorkloadManager as Deployment with Redis connection\n  3. Sandbox Pods with optional PicoD sidecar\n- **AND** each deployment pattern has resource requirements and scaling notes\n\n---\n\n## REQ-002: Component Architecture Documentation\n\n### Description\n\nDocument each major system component with detailed architecture, responsibilities, and integration points.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Router component architecture page exists\n- **GIVEN** the architecture documentation directory\n- **WHEN** a user views the Router component page (`router.md`)\n- **THEN** the document explains Router's role:\n  - Session routing and reverse proxy\n  - JWT token validation\n  - Traffic routing to sandbox pods\n- **AND** the page includes:\n  - Request flow diagram\n  - Session management logic description\n  - Supported endpoints table (`/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path`)\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager component documentation\n- **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n- **WHEN** a user views the WorkloadManager component page (`workloadmanager.md`)\n- **THEN** the document describes:\n  - Sandbox lifecycle management (create, delete, garbage collection)\n  - Kubernetes API interactions (CRDs, Pods, Secrets)\n  - Health check and metrics endpoints\n- **AND** includes endpoint documentation:\n  - `/sandboxes` POST (create sandbox)\n  - `/sandboxes/:id` GET/DELETE\n  - `/health/live` and `/health/ready`\n\n#### Scenario: PicoD daemon architecture documented\n- **GIVEN** the architecture documentation directory\n- **WHEN** a user views the PicoD component page (`picod.md`)\n- **THEN** the document explains:\n  - Local code execution daemon running as sidecar\n  - Workspace isolation and sanitization\n  - File operations (upload, download, list)\n  - Code execution timeout management\n- **AND** provides endpoint details:\n  - `/api/execute` POST for code execution\n  - `/api/files` POST/GET for file operations\n\n#### Scenario: Agentd idle cleanup controller documented\n- **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n- **WHEN** the Agentd component page (`agentd.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document explains:\n  - Kubernetes controller-runtime architecture\n  - Idle threshold detection logic\n  - Leader election for singleton controller\n  - Cleanup workflow steps\n- **AND** includes configuration parameters documentation:\n  - `--idle-threshold` (default 30m)\n  - `--check-interval` (default 5m)\n  - `--leader-election` flag\n\n---\n\n## REQ-003: Data Flow Documentation\n\n### Description\n\nDocument how data flows through the system for key operations (sandbox creation, code execution, session routing).\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox creation flow documented\n- **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n- **WHEN** the data flow section is viewed\n- **THEN** a step-by-step flow diagram exists for sandbox creation:\n  1. SDK → Router (JWT authenticated request)\n  2. Router → WorkloadManager (sandbox creation request)\n  3. WorkloadManager → Kubernetes API (create Pod, Secret, CRDs)\n  4. WorkloadManager → Router (return sandbox endpoint)\n  5. Router → SDK (session response with sandbox URL)\n- **AND** each step includes timeout and retry behavior notes\n\n#### Scenario: Code execution flow documented\n- **GIVEN** the data flow documentation\n- **WHEN** the code execution flow page is viewed\n- **THEN** the document shows the execution flow:\n  1. Client sends code via Router to sandbox pod\n  2. Router validates JWT and routes to correct sandbox\n  3. PicoD receives request in sandbox pod\n  4. PicoD executes code with workspace isolation\n  5. Response returns through Router to client\n- **AND** includes error handling scenarios:\n  - Timeout during execution\n  - Sandbox pod not ready\n  - Invalid authentication token\n\n#### Scenario: Session routing flow documented\n- **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n- **WHEN** the session routing flow section is viewed\n- **THEN** the document explains how Router maintains session state:\n  - Redis/Valkey stores session-to-sandbox mappings\n  - Session key structure documented (`session:<id>`)\n  - Session TTL and cleanup logic\n- **AND** includes session lifecycle states:\n  - Created, Active, Expired, Terminated\n\n---\n\n## REQ-004: Python SDK API Documentation\n\n### Description\n\nProvide complete API documentation for the Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) with code examples and type signatures.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Python SDK overview page exists\n- **GIVEN** the API documentation directory at `docs/docs/api/sdk-python/`\n- **WHEN** a user navigates to the SDK overview (`overview.md`)\n- **THEN** the page includes:\n  - Installation instructions (`pip install agentcube-sdk`)\n  - Quick start code example\n  - SDK architecture diagram showing Control Plane vs Data Plane\n  - Version compatibility table\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterClient API documented\n- **GIVEN** the Python SDK API documentation\n- **WHEN** a user views the CodeInterpreterClient API page (`code-interpreter-client.md`)\n- **THEN** the document provides complete API reference:\n  - Class initialization parameters (`router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `jwt_token`)\n  - `execute_code(language, code, timeout)` method signature and return type\n  - `execute_command(command)` method signature\n  - `upload_file(path, content)` method\n  - `download_file(path)` method\n  - `list_files()` method\n  - `create_session()` and `stop_session()` methods\n- **AND** each method includes:\n  - Type annotations (Python 3.10+)\n  - Parameter descriptions\n  - Return value documentation\n  - Exception types that can be raised\n  - Code example snippet\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient API documented\n- **GIVEN** the Python SDK API documentation\n- **WHEN** the AgentRuntimeClient API page (`agent-runtime-client.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document includes:\n  - Client initialization parameters\n  - `invoke_agent(agent_name, input_data)` method\n  - Session management for agent invocations\n  - Response format documentation\n- **AND** provides examples for:\n  - Basic agent invocation\n  - Session reuse with multiple invocations\n  - Error handling patterns\n\n#### Scenario: Exception hierarchy documented\n- **GIVEN** the Python SDK API documentation\n- **WHEN** a user views the exceptions page (`exceptions.md`)\n- **THEN** the document lists all exception types:\n  - `AgentCubeError` (base exception)\n  - `CommandExecutionError` (code/command failures)\n  - `SessionError` (session lifecycle errors)\n  - `DataPlaneError` (PicoD communication errors)\n  - `AuthenticationError` (JWT validation failures)\n- **AND** each exception includes:\n  - Inheritance hierarchy\n  - Exception attributes (e.g., `exit_code`, `stderr` for CommandExecutionError)\n  - Example code showing how to catch and handle the exception\n\n#### Scenario: Session management patterns documented\n- **GIVEN** the Python SDK documentation\n- **WHEN** the session management page (`sessions.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document explains:\n  - Session creation and configuration options\n  - Session reuse with context manager pattern\n  - Explicit session termination\n  - Session timeout behavior\n- **AND** provides code examples:\n  ```python\n  # Context manager pattern\n  with CodeInterpreterClient(...) as client:\n      client.execute_code(\"python\", \"print('hello')\")\n  # Explicit session management\n  client = CodeInterpreterClient(...)\n  session = client.create_session()\n  client.execute_code(\"python\", \"code\", session_id=session.id)\n  client.stop_session(session.id)\n  ```\n\n---\n\n## REQ-005: Go Client API Documentation\n\n### Description\n\nProvide complete API documentation for the Go client (`client-go`) with Kubernetes-native patterns and type signatures.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Go client overview page exists\n- **GIVEN** the API documentation directory at `docs/docs/api/client-go/`\n- **WHEN** a user navigates to the Go client overview (`overview.md`)\n- **THEN** the page includes:\n  - Installation via Go module (`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`)\n  - Kubernetes client-go integration explanation\n  - CRD types (`AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter`)\n  - Version compatibility with Kubernetes versions\n\n#### Scenario: Clientset construction documented\n- **GIVEN** the Go client API documentation\n- **WHEN** a user views the Clientset documentation (`clientset.md`)\n- **THEN** the document provides:\n  - `NewForConfig(config *rest.Config)` function signature\n  - `NewForConfigOrDie(config)` panic variant\n  - Clientset interface methods (`RuntimeV1alpha1()`, `Discovery()`)\n- **AND** includes code example:\n  ```go\n  config, err := clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", kubeconfigPath)\n  clientset, err := clientset.NewForConfig(config)\n  runtimeClient := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace)\n  ```\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRUD operations documented\n- **GIVEN** the Go client API documentation\n- **WHEN** the AgentRuntime operations page (`agent-runtime-crud.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document lists all CRUD methods:\n  - `Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n  - `Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})`\n  - `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n  - `Update(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n  - `UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n  - `Delete(ctx, name, metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n  - `DeleteCollection(ctx, metav1.DeleteOptions{}, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n  - `Patch(ctx, name, patchType, patch, metav1.PatchOptions{})`\n  - `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n- **AND** each method includes:\n  - Go type signatures\n  - Parameter descriptions\n  - Return types and errors\n  - Code example\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRUD operations documented\n- **GIVEN** the Go client API documentation\n- **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter operations page (`code-interpreter-crud.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document mirrors AgentRuntime CRUD documentation structure\n- **AND** includes examples for all CRUD operations on CodeInterpreter resources\n\n#### Scenario: Informer and Lister patterns documented\n- **GIVEN** the Go client API documentation\n- **WHEN** the informer documentation page (`informer.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document explains:\n  - `SharedInformerFactory` construction\n  - `Start(stopCh)` and `Shutdown()` methods\n  - `WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)` for cache synchronization\n  - AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter informers\n  - Lister interface usage patterns\n- **AND** provides code examples:\n  ```go\n  factory := externalversions.NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, 30*time.Second)\n  informer := factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes()\n  stopCh := make(chan struct{})\n  factory.Start(stopCh)\n  factory.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)\n  lister := informer.Lister()\n  ar, err := lister.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(name)\n  ```\n\n#### Scenario: Fake clientset for testing documented\n- **GIVEN** the Go client API documentation\n- **WHEN** the testing page (`testing.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document explains:\n  - `NewSimpleClientset()` for unit testing\n  - Adding reactors for custom behavior\n  - Object tracking and retrieval\n  - Watch simulation in tests\n- **AND** includes test example code snippet\n\n---\n\n## REQ-006: CRD Schema Documentation\n\n### Description\n\nDocument the Kubernetes Custom Resource Definition schemas for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD schema documented\n- **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n- **WHEN** a user views the CRD schema page (`crd-agent-runtime.md`)\n- **THEN** the document includes:\n  - Full YAML schema example\n  - Spec fields documentation:\n    - `replicas` (integer, default 1)\n    - `image` (string, required)\n    - `resources` (ResourceRequirements)\n    - `env` (array of EnvVar)\n    - `volumeMounts` (array)\n  - Status fields documentation:\n    - `phase` (Running, Pending, Failed)\n    - `conditions` (array of Condition)\n    - `podName` (string)\n- **AND** includes validation rules and default values\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD schema documented\n- **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n- **WHEN** a user views the CodeInterpreter CRD schema (`crd-code-interpreter.md`)\n- **THEN** the document provides:\n  - Full YAML schema example\n  - Spec fields:\n    - `language` (python, javascript, typescript)\n    - `timeout` (duration string)\n    - `workspaceSize` (resource quantity)\n  - Status fields:\n    - `sessionID` (string)\n    - `podIP` (string)\n    - `lastExecutionTime` (timestamp)\n- **AND** includes example YAML manifest\n\n#### Scenario: CRD API version documented\n- **GIVEN** the CRD documentation\n- **WHEN** the API version section is viewed\n- **THEN** the document states the API group and version:\n  - API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n  - Version: `v1alpha1`\n- **AND** explains version stability status and future versioning plans\n\n---\n\n## REQ-007: Configuration Documentation\n\n### Description\n\nDocument configuration options for each binary component with command-line flags and environment variables.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Router configuration documented\n- **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n- **WHEN** the Router configuration page (`router-config.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document lists all configuration options:\n  - `--port` (default :8080)\n  - `--store-addr` (Redis address)\n  - `--store-type` (redis/valkey)\n  - `--max-concurrent` (default 1000)\n  - `--enable-tls` and `--tls-cert/--tls-key`\n  - Environment variable overrides (`PORT`, `STORE_ADDR`, `STORE_TYPE`)\n- **AND** each option includes:\n  - Default value\n  - Valid values/ranges\n  - Usage description\n  - Example command line\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager configuration documented\n- **GIVEN** the configuration documentation\n- **WHEN** the WorkloadManager configuration page (`workloadmanager-config.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document lists:\n  - `--addr` (HTTP server address)\n  - `--gc-interval` (garbage collection interval, default 5m)\n  - `--kubeconfig` (Kubernetes config path)\n  - HTTP timeout configurations (`--read-timeout`, `--write-timeout`)\n- **AND** provides example deployment YAML with configuration\n\n#### Scenario: PicoD configuration documented\n- **GIVEN** the configuration documentation\n- **WHEN** the PicoD configuration page (`picod-config.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document includes:\n  - `--port` (default 8080)\n  - `--workspace` (workspace directory path)\n  - `--auth-enabled` (JWT authentication toggle)\n  - `--max-exec-time` (execution timeout, default 30s)\n  - `--max-file-size` (file size limit, default 10MB)\n  - `--sanitize-root` (path sanitization root)\n- **AND** includes security configuration best practices\n\n#### Scenario: Agentd configuration documented\n- **GIVEN** the configuration documentation\n- **WHEN** the Agentd configuration page (`agentd-config.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document lists:\n  - `--idle-threshold` (default 30m)\n  - `--check-interval` (default 5m)\n  - `--max-concurrent-cleanup` (default 10)\n  - `--leader-election` (default true)\n  - `--namespace` (watched namespaces)\n- **AND** explains leader election configuration\n\n---\n\n## REQ-008: Deployment Documentation\n\n### Description\n\nProvide deployment guides for installing AgentCube on Kubernetes with Helm charts.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Helm installation guide documented\n- **GIVEN** the deployment documentation directory at `docs/docs/deployment/`\n- **WHEN** the Helm installation page (`helm-installation.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document provides:\n  - Helm chart location\n  - Installation command: `helm install agentcube ./manifests/helm/agentcube`\n  - Required values configuration:\n    - Redis/Valkey connection settings\n    - JWT configuration\n    - Kubernetes namespace\n  - Optional values table\n- **AND** includes post-installation verification steps\n\n#### Scenario: Prerequisites documented\n- **GIVEN** the deployment documentation\n- **WHEN** the prerequisites page (`prerequisites.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document lists:\n  - Kubernetes version requirements (≥1.24)\n  - Required cluster resources (CPU, memory)\n  - Redis/Valkey deployment\n  - Helm 3 installation\n  - kubectl configuration\n- **AND** provides setup commands for each prerequisite\n\n#### Scenario: Multi-namespace deployment documented\n- **GIVEN** the deployment documentation\n- **WHEN** the multi-namespace deployment page (`multi-namespace.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document explains:\n  - Deploying Router and WorkloadManager in separate namespaces\n  - Cross-namespace communication configuration\n  - RBAC requirements for multi-namespace access\n- **AND** includes YAML examples for namespace-scoped deployment\n\n#### Scenario: TLS and security configuration documented\n- **GIVEN** the deployment documentation\n- **WHEN** the security configuration page (`security.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document provides:\n  - TLS certificate configuration for Router\n  - JWT signing key management\n  - RBAC configuration for WorkloadManager\n  - Network policies for pod isolation\n  - Secret management best practices\n- **AND** includes example YAML configurations for each security setting\n\n---\n\n## REQ-009: Examples and Tutorials\n\n### Description\n\nProvide example applications and tutorials demonstrating AgentCube usage patterns.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: PCAP analyzer example documented\n- **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n- **WHEN** the examples page (`examples.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document includes:\n  - PCAP analyzer application description\n  - Architecture diagram showing LangChain + AgentCube integration\n  - Setup and deployment instructions\n  - Code walkthrough for key components\n- **AND** provides link to full source code in `example/pcap-analyzer/`\n\n#### Scenario: Quick start tutorial documented\n- **GIVEN** the getting-started documentation\n- **WHEN** the quick start tutorial (`first-sandbox.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document provides step-by-step guide:\n  1. Install AgentCube via Helm\n  2. Configure Python SDK connection\n  3. Create first sandbox session\n  4. Execute Python code\n  5. Upload and download files\n  6. Clean up session\n- **AND** each step includes code examples and expected output\n\n#### Scenario: LangChain integration tutorial documented\n- **GIVEN** the examples documentation\n- **WHEN** the LangChain integration page (`langchain-tutorial.md`) is viewed\n- **THEN** the document provides:\n  - LangChain tool wrapper implementation\n  - Agent workflow with code execution\n  - Session management in multi-turn conversations\n  - Error handling patterns\n- **AND** includes runnable code snippets\n\n---\n\n## REQ-010: Documentation Navigation and Cross-References\n\n### Description\n\nEnsure documentation has proper navigation structure and cross-references between related topics.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Sidebar navigation configured correctly\n- **GIVEN** the Docusaurus sidebars configuration at `docs/sidebars.ts`\n- **WHEN** the sidebars configuration is viewed\n- **THEN** the file includes:\n  - `architecture` sidebar with autogenerated directory\n  - `api` sidebar with Python SDK and Go Client categories\n  - `deployment` sidebar for deployment guides\n- **AND** each sidebar category has proper labels and descriptions\n\n#### Scenario: Architecture to API cross-references exist\n- **GIVEN** the architecture documentation pages\n- **WHEN** an architecture page discusses a component\n- **THEN** the page includes Docusaurus links to relevant API documentation:\n  - Router architecture → Go Client router endpoints\n  - PicoD architecture → Python SDK code execution API\n  - CRD architecture → Go Client CRUD operations\n- **AND** links use proper Docusaurus link syntax\n\n#### Scenario: API to deployment cross-references exist\n- **GIVEN** the API documentation pages\n- **WHEN** an API page documents client configuration\n- **THEN** the page links to deployment configuration documentation\n- **AND** includes links to Helm value configuration\n\n#### Scenario: Documentation index page exists\n- **GIVEN** the documentation site\n- **WHEN** a user visits the documentation root\n- **THEN** an index page (`docs/docs/intro.md`) exists\n- **AND** the page provides:\n  - Overview of AgentCube\n  - Quick links to Getting Started, Architecture, API, Deployment\n  - Documentation structure diagram\n\n---\n\n## REQ-011: Documentation Quality and Completeness\n\n### Description\n\nEnsure documentation meets quality standards for technical accuracy, readability, and completeness.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: All API methods are documented\n- **GIVEN** the Python SDK source code at `sdk-python/`\n- **WHEN** documentation generation is verified\n- **THEN** every public class method in `CodeInterpreterClient` has a documentation entry\n- **AND** every public method in `AgentRuntimeClient` has a documentation entry\n- **AND** documentation coverage metric is ≥90%\n\n#### Scenario: Documentation builds without errors\n- **GIVEN** the Docusaurus documentation site\n- **WHEN** `npm run build` is executed in the `docs/` directory\n- **THEN** the build succeeds with no errors\n- **AND** all pages are generated correctly\n- **AND** no broken internal links are reported\n\n#### Scenario: Code examples are runnable\n- **GIVEN** the documentation code examples\n- **WHEN** code examples are tested against a running AgentCube instance\n- **THEN** at least 80% of code examples execute successfully\n- **AND** examples use realistic parameters and values\n- **AND** examples include necessary import statements\n\n#### Scenario: Documentation is version-controlled\n- **GIVEN** the documentation files\n- **WHEN** git history is examined\n- **THEN** all documentation files are tracked in version control\n- **AND** documentation changes are reviewed via pull request process\n- **AND** significant documentation updates are mentioned in changelog\n\n#### Scenario: Documentation has consistent formatting\n- **GIVEN** all documentation markdown files\n- **WHEN** formatting is validated\n- **THEN** all files use consistent markdown style:\n  - Headers use ATX style (# syntax)\n  - Code blocks have language annotations\n  - Tables use GitHub-flavored markdown syntax\n  - Lists use consistent indentation (2 spaces)\n- **AND** Docusaurus frontmatter (`id`, `title`, `description`) is present where required\n\n---\n\n## REQ-012: Internationalization Support\n\n### Description\n\nProvide documentation in multiple languages (English as primary, with structure for translations).\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: English documentation is primary\n- **GIVEN** the documentation directory\n- **WHEN** the default documentation locale is examined\n- **THEN** all documentation files are written in English\n- **AND** English is configured as default locale in `docusaurus.config.ts`\n\n#### Scenario: Translation structure exists\n- **GIVEN** the Docusaurus i18n configuration at `docs/i18n/`\n- **WHEN** the i18n directory structure is examined\n- **THEN** the directory structure supports translations:\n  - `i18n/zh-CN/` for Chinese translation\n  - `i18n/ja/` for Japanese translation\n- **AND** translation JSON files for UI strings exist\n\n#### Scenario: Locale configuration is correct\n- **GIVEN** the Docusaurus config\n- **WHEN** `i18n` configuration is examined\n- **THEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` includes:\n  - `defaultLocale: 'en'`\n  - `locales: ['en', 'zh-CN', 'ja']`\n  - Locale names and labels configured\n- **AND** locale switcher UI is enabled\n\n---\n\n## REQ-013: Documentation Search and Indexing\n\n### Description\n\nEnable documentation search functionality for users to find relevant content quickly.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Documentation search is enabled\n- **GIVEN** the Docusaurus configuration\n- **WHEN** search configuration is examined\n- **THEN** a search plugin is configured (e.g., Algolia or local search)\n- **AND** search input is visible in documentation navbar\n\n#### Scenario: Search indexes all documentation pages\n- **GIVEN** the search configuration\n- **WHEN** search functionality is tested\n- **THEN** search results include:\n  - Architecture documentation pages\n  - API documentation pages\n  - Deployment guides\n  - Getting started pages\n- **AND** search results show page titles and relevant excerpts\n\n#### Scenario: API methods are searchable\n- **GIVEN** the documentation search\n- **WHEN** a user searches for \"execute_code\"\n- **THEN** the search returns results pointing to:\n  - Python SDK code execution documentation\n  - Code execution flow architecture\n  - Quick start tutorial with execute_code example\n- **AND** search results are ranked by relevance\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| REQ ID | Component | Deliverables |\n|--------|-----------|--------------|\n| REQ-001 | Architecture Overview | `overview.md` with system diagram and tech stack |\n| REQ-002 | Component Architecture | `router.md`, `workloadmanager.md`, `picod.md`, `agentd.md` |\n| REQ-003 | Data Flow | Sandbox creation, code execution, session routing flows |\n| REQ-004 | Python SDK API | `overview.md`, `code-interpreter-client.md`, `agent-runtime-client.md`, `exceptions.md`, `sessions.md` |\n| REQ-005 | Go Client API | `overview.md`, `clientset.md`, CRUD docs, `informer.md`, `testing.md` |\n| REQ-006 | CRD Schema | `crd-agent-runtime.md`, `crd-code-interpreter.md` |\n| REQ-007 | Configuration | Config docs for Router, WorkloadManager, PicoD, Agentd |\n| REQ-008 | Deployment | Helm guide, prerequisites, multi-namespace, security |\n| REQ-009 | Examples | PCAP analyzer, quick start, LangChain tutorial |\n| REQ-010 | Navigation | Sidebar config, cross-references, index page |\n| REQ-011 | Quality | API coverage, build success, runnable examples |\n| REQ-012 | Internationalization | English primary, translation structure |\n| REQ-013 | Search | Search plugin configuration and indexing |\n\n**Total Requirements:** 13  \n**Total Scenarios:** 48\n\n---\n\n## Documentation File Structure\n\n```\ndocs/docs/\n├── architecture/\n│   ├── overview.md                 (REQ-001)\n│   ├── router.md                   (REQ-002)\n│   ├── workloadmanager.md          (REQ-002)\n│   ├── picod.md                    (REQ-002)\n│   ├── agentd.md                   (REQ-002)\n│   ├── data-flow/\n│   │   ├── sandbox-creation.md     (REQ-003)\n│   │   ├── code-execution.md       (REQ-003)\n│   │   └── session-routing.md      (REQ-003)\n│   └── crd/\n│       ├── agent-runtime.md        (REQ-006)\n│       └── code-interpreter.md     (REQ-006)\n│\n├── api/\n│   ├── sdk-python/\n│   │   ├── overview.md             (REQ-004)\n│   │   ├── code-interpreter-client.md (REQ-004)\n│   │   ├── agent-runtime-client.md    (REQ-004)\n│   │   ├── exceptions.md           (REQ-004)\n│   │   └── sessions.md             (REQ-004)\n│   └── client-go/\n│       ├── overview.md             (REQ-005)\n│       ├── clientset.md            (REQ-005)\n│       ├── agent-runtime-crud.md   (REQ-005)\n│       ├── code-interpreter-crud.md (REQ-005)\n│       ├── informer.md             (REQ-005)\n│       └── testing.md              (REQ-005)\n│\n├── deployment/\n│   ├── helm-installation.md        (REQ-008)\n│   ├── prerequisites.md            (REQ-008)\n│   ├── multi-namespace.md          (REQ-008)\n│   ├── security.md                 (REQ-008)\n│   ├── config/\n│   │   ├── router-config.md        (REQ-007)\n│   │   ├── workloadmanager-config.md (REQ-007)\n│   │   ├── picod-config.md         (REQ-007)\n│   │   └── agentd-config.md        (REQ-007)\n│\n├── examples/\n│   ├── overview.md                 (REQ-009)\n│   ├── pcap-analyzer.md            (REQ-009)\n│   ├── langchain-tutorial.md       (REQ-009)\n│\n└── intro.md                        (REQ-010)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| Docusaurus 3.x | Documentation site generator |\n| Node.js ≥18 | Docusaurus runtime |\n| npm | Package management |\n| Mermaid | Diagram rendering (optional) |\n| Algolia DocSearch | Search plugin (optional) |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Architecture overview page exists with system diagram\n- [ ] Router component architecture documented\n- [ ] WorkloadManager component architecture documented\n- [ ] PicoD daemon architecture documented\n- [ ] Agentd controller architecture documented\n- [ ] Sandbox creation data flow documented\n- [ ] Code execution data flow documented\n- [ ] Session routing data flow documented\n- [ ] Python SDK overview documented\n- [ ] CodeInterpreterClient API fully documented\n- [ ] AgentRuntimeClient API fully documented\n- [ ] Exception hierarchy documented\n- [ ] Session management patterns documented\n- [ ] Go client overview documented\n- [ ] Clientset construction documented\n- [ ] AgentRuntime CRUD operations documented\n- [ ] CodeInterpreter CRUD operations documented\n- [ ] Informer and Lister patterns documented\n- [ ] Fake clientset testing documented\n- [ ] AgentRuntime CRD schema do